			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=348#M348">126</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>The problem is class-balancing is that there are too many classes. The SoE marketing department may have needed Berzerkers to sell an expansion, but the game itself didn't. We long ago reached the point where Beastlords are an upgrade&nbsp;replacement for&nbsp;Shaman in all but a few very high end situations. Warriors lobbied as a class and screwed over the SKs and Paladins. There aren't enough Clerics on most servers, but Clerics jealously resist other classes being given sufficient heals to replace them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If the spell immunity check and other aggro nerfs go through, there'll be little reason for Paladins to continue to play EQ. The Pally defensive disclipline is already a bad joke, a false promise of a significant new ability that maybe helped sell a few more units of the DoN expansion. With Pallies an obsolete class, SKs will soon following them out the door to other games. Hey, no problem. Monks are tanks again!</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-15-2005</span> <span class=time_text>06:25 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
