		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I play a mage, what they are proposing for us at this point is as useless as the jewelry bags that we summon once or twice a year.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I no longer solo. I do group with a druid for the snare and the fact she can heal my pet, between the two of us we have a good chance at keeping it alive.&nbsp;Mages have no heal to speak of. 1,200 hps compared to the beastlords 2.7k pet heal and it takes for ever to be able to recast it. Chain cast pets, sure. At the speed that unsnared mobs move and the lag that is in most of the zones you're hammered before you get the pet casted. If you're lucky you can continue your cast and run away until your unbuffed, unarmed pet gains aggro. You better be casting another by then. At the end of this you are near oom and way down in hitpoints so have to sit for 5-10 minutes to med and heal up. And for a pittance of exp.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>LFG for hours on end just to see other classes taken. You hear people asking for tanks, healers and slowers all the time, well mages do none of the above. Nuking? yes I can nuke, when my fire nukes don't get resisted by mobs that are immune to fire spells. Oh thats right I can use magic based nukes which do only about half the damage my fire nukes do. That makes me much less effective than wizards or druids in those zones. I'm not asking to be the nuke king, that crown should rightly set on the head of the wizards, but let me do something besides summon mod rods.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Pets not causing problems on raids, get real. For some reason pets take a dislike to a certain mob and all the pet holds and back offs won't get it to change its target. But by then its to late and you've trained your raid or group. A way of actually erasing a pets hate list would be great. And the lack of pet healing for us effects our dps output since we have to recast our pet, reshrink it , rearm it and rebuff it. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If the change goes thru the way it sounds Pallies and SKs and to some extent Warriors are getting shafted big time. Please don't remove the aggro they generate by using spells &amp; procs that mobs are immune to. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as Druids I don't see a reason to punish them by removing mana from them but once they choose to use one of the options grey out the abilities for a time, perhaps 20 minutes or so. This would allow some flexibility but would not allow for an abuse of the increases they would receive.&nbsp; Yeah and their pet really does suck. A better pet that can actually do a bit of damage would be a big help.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mainly don't nerf the aggro tools the tanks have, erase a pets hate list when you tell them to back off and give mages something useful like an honest to god pet heal spell similiar to the beastlords. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
