<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=353#M353">132</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Edit of druid class changes, to fit all classes for an option to solo.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>**&nbsp; Introduce a new option where <STRONG>any class </STRONG>can enter into a particular "<STRONG>mode</STRONG>" or "<STRONG>stance</STRONG>" (<STRONG>status</STRONG>) where they become better at defense or offense at the expense of the other, in addition to "normal" <STRONG>status</STRONG>.&nbsp;&nbsp; You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 3-5 minutes.</DIV>
<DIV>- You may also&nbsp;switch to&nbsp;an innate ability, or spell, (switched with a spell you use often),&nbsp;which you may not presently have, activated by&nbsp;being in the&nbsp; <STRONG>status</STRONG> you chose.</DIV>- This will be similar to creating a new character, you will be able to alter your abilities at the cost of one, to advance in another you feel would help your class become more effective.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>- </DIV></DIV>
<DIV>1.&nbsp; You must diminish one ability or stat, to gain available points to use&nbsp;in another area.</DIV>
<DIV>2.&nbsp; The stats you change&nbsp;will be intensified when soloing, or not in a group by approximately 30%.</DIV>
<DIV>3.&nbsp; Then you can apply this "<STRONG>status</STRONG>"&nbsp; to a button, which would work similar to abilities such as backstab or track, and also similar to changing gear, with the new equipment packs.</DIV>
<DIV>4.&nbsp; There will be two different <STRONG>status'</STRONG> which you can do this for.</DIV>
<DIV>5.&nbsp; When you switch from one status, where you may have less mana, you will have to meditate to gain that mana back.</DIV>
<DIV>6.&nbsp; This will only be used for base stats, not with AA or other points where you have abilities gained.</DIV>
<DIV>7.&nbsp; There will be a limit on stats that you can diminish, and what you can diminish or add to.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This way, it will be up to <STRONG>you</STRONG> what you can do to better yourself.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<P>Blue.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Normal  Their healing and offensive abilities are in balance.&nbsp; This is the state they exist in today.</P>
<P>Red.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Offensive  Their offensive power is boosted by 30%, but they suffer a 30% reduction in the defensive power.</P>
<P>Green.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Defensive  Their healing power is boosted by 30%, but they suffer a 30% reduction in the offensive power.</P>
<P>Options for others may come later.</P>
<P>** Broaden the core grouping roles to allow all classes to more easily put together groups.&nbsp; Similar to how any of the 3 main tanks should be able to perform that role in a group, we want any of the 3 healers to be able to perform the role of a main healer in a group.&nbsp; The changes mentioned above for druids will allow you to fill a healing role and perform at about 80% of the effectiveness of a cleric.</P>
<P>In conjunction with spreading spell progression out for levels 1 to 50 to reduce the levels gaps between gaining new spells.&nbsp; We would like casters to gain new spells every level and enjoy more even progression.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>** Lowering the level requirement for Aegolism, KEI and other spells, or making new spells within those lines with increased duration.</P>
<P>We are planning to add new abilities and disciplines to non-casters and spread those out between levels 1 to 50, along with their current abilities to make sure non-casters also have progression, in the form of a new ability, every level.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-15-2005</span> <span class=time_text>07:32 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
