		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I posted some of this on the enchanter boards but I feel the need to re-post it here.&nbsp; Charming was a vital role of enchanters, and while *some* (vxed/tipt) encounters allowed for very overpowered pets, for the most part the risk vs. reward in past times was about right... it still took group effort to keep pets in viable zones under control.&nbsp;&nbsp; The OOW mez changes destroyed any chances I had at soloing. Period.&nbsp; Not just soloing efficiently, if my summoned swords can't kill it, neither can a charmed pet now.</DIV>
<DIV>I loved my class and I stayed with it even though charming was what got me playing an enchanter.&nbsp; LFG times went through the roof due to mezzes being buried (turned down for groups left and right because everyone wanted to go to zones in which I couldn't mez).&nbsp; When playing my cleric alt in zones like RCoD, mobs mitigated slow so much that I couldn't tell if a slow had landed or not, it made no difference to how I needed to heal.&nbsp; With the resist rates on mez, and the subsequent enchanter deaths following, in-camp CC is not viable.&nbsp; When the enchanter dies the group wipes to adds.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>Bards are already widely chosen over enchanters.&nbsp; C3 is bought in PoK, our group roles are dwindling.&nbsp; Soloing is a no go.&nbsp; I loved the necro Screaming Terror line, now I fear it because it lowers our desireability even more, the same goes for beastlord slows.</DIV>
<DIV>I am not a buff bot.&nbsp; I don't want to farm pp in PoK casting my 4.5 hour c3.&nbsp; It's not why I play.&nbsp; I love this game and I've played for&nbsp;over 5 years now.&nbsp; The erosion of class abilities with none to replace it, however, gives us&nbsp;three options: (1) retire (2) buff bot and shoosh (3) break out a good book for all the hours in the guild hall LFG.</DIV>
<DIV>Class unique abilities was always in my opinion one of the great things about this game, I hope it continues to follow that path rather than further blurring class lines.&nbsp; I'm not a wizard nor am I a warrior - and I like it that way <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Erowydd</DIV>
<DIV>70 Bedazzler - Quellious Server</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
