			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=354#M354">136</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>The idea for druids was to make a&nbsp;druid that can fill a healer spot well, like the way an sk can fill a tank spot well in groups.&nbsp; Having a better druid doesn't threaten clerics, it just provides another option.&nbsp; In areas where the tank is paper, the cleric still reigns supreme.&nbsp; In areas where the tank is ok, a druid can heal with slightly more med time.&nbsp; Incidentally, a druid would still have a harder time even with the cleric CH because they lack the top notch buffs that a cleric has, and symbol/wov&nbsp;are rather short duration to beg off of someone.</P>
<P>As for druid dps, ancient oow wizzy nukes are 1785/292 (6.11) and 4070/850 (4.79)&nbsp;unfocused, both classes get the same focuses so it doesn't matter.</P>
<P>Ancient oow druid nuke is 2302/517 (4.45). 69 dot is 5*412/441 (4.67). Add 25% and you get (5.57) or (5.84), plus the side effects of buffs, mini rezzes (which preserve the target's mana),&nbsp;and heals while the cleric is medding.&nbsp; That gives wizzies about 7% more dps than druids in nuke mode (assuming druid dots and nukes once per mob, which is a bit arbitrary).&nbsp; All the nonsense about wizzies having 10k+ nukes is absolutely meaningless; you aren't going to kill a group mob in one hit, so who cares? Rogues backstab for maybe 4k, but they are still top notch dps.</P>
<P>If you have a good tank/cleric combo&nbsp;already, a wizzy is slightly better for dps but not hugely better, and a 500 aa druid would beat a 100 aa wizzy most likely; if you have a bad tank or a weak cleric, a druid is better.&nbsp;There's nothing really new there, except that druids get enough dps to be useful.&nbsp;Considering the way most hybrid tanks think they are underpowered, they probably want the extra buffage (as a bard i know i want steel).</P>
<P>The way the toggle mode hits hard is that when a druid does&nbsp;spot heals on the puller, for example,&nbsp;and a cleric handles chs, the druids effectiveness will drop dramatically. 2420/627 will halve to 1210/627,&nbsp;leaving the poor druid with a 1.93 ratio.&nbsp; Thats a sadder ratio than a ranger (680/245 = 2.78), bst, pally... you get the picture.&nbsp; Perhaps only cut heal over times or something to a 35% drop, so that the druid can heal the group reasonably well but wouldn't be main healing and in high dps mode at the same time.</P>
<P>Overall: druids are a very good dps class and a viable healer, but a cleric still has a&nbsp;decent advantage in healing and pure dps classes still have a slight edge.&nbsp; That's what I'll think when i check lfg.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
