		" 
			>
			<DIV>On the enchanter thing again... sounds like people are complaining about the old charm and think the new pet buff idea is "stupid".&nbsp; Sounds to me like the charm has the buff as part of it, so you cast the same number of spells; it should be easy.&nbsp; Throwing in some numbers... 1000 dps mob (made up number for ease of calculation).&nbsp; Charm pet = 50% or 500 dps, haste pet buff = 70% = 850 dps.&nbsp; Regular mob = 1000 dps, slowed for 35% (partial slow, not sure if that number is correct) = 650 dps.&nbsp; Charm pet wins all by itself, and your dps will make it go down fast.&nbsp; Early charm breaking&nbsp; = pain, but that's always true.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you wanna try some really advanced stuff, don't slow the mob, tash it at some point, and nuke carefully so both mobs drop at about the same speed.&nbsp; Mez the regular mob so it lands at 5%, you tashed it so mez should land reliably (if it doesn't, you just killed a mob, oh no).&nbsp; Your charm pet will back off now, get some distance, break charm, and nuke it to death.&nbsp; Runes will most likely drop in the process, but you should get 100% xp.&nbsp; Nuke the mezzed mob to death (should take 1 nuke i think) and you have killed 2 mobs, solo, with about&nbsp;1000 dps on both of em.&nbsp; Maybe the charm pet will take some xp on the other mob, maybe it won't because it's dead.&nbsp; Sounds pretty good to me either way.&nbsp; Now, since I'm a bard and things work kinda differently for bards, feel free to ignore me, but think about it before flaming please.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
