<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=360#M360">138</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Blah Sks getting the shaft again it seems. Why is it that Sks are the only class other than Rangers&nbsp;that don't have ALL the various powers of their parent classes in some form? No matter how lesser the spells/powers all other hybrids can do all the things their parents classes can.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;Examples:&nbsp;Paladins can heal,&nbsp;rezz to 90% and buff you with a virtue like hp buffs. </DIV>
<DIV>Beastlords have a 65% slow, can buff you almost as well as thier shammy parent, have cleric like heals for their pets&nbsp;and have a seriously nasty pet. </DIV>
<DIV>Rangers can harmony like druids, they have better track than druids, they forage, snares and roots, they have lesser heals, lesser nukes and&nbsp;buffs. The only thing they can't do that a druid can do is port&nbsp; and&nbsp;gate. And they should have either a self port or gate.</DIV>
<DIV>Shadowknights&nbsp;on the other hand, don't even come close to the same hps as warriors, they can't mez not even with a lower level screaming terror type spell like necros, can't slow undead like necros, can't rez like necros - not even theirselves -&nbsp;and they&nbsp;can't charm like necros. Basically the only things we have from the parent class we are often most associated with (necromancers)&nbsp;is much weeker snares with dots on them, much weaker dots, extremely weak lifetaps, a type of lich at the highest levels only and feign death.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In the "Everquest Runes of Kunark" book, sanctioned by SoE, it says: "Shadow Knights are designed to be the most offense-directed class in the game. Everything about a Shadow Knight is focused on overpowering your target with the combination of strength, spells, pets, lifetaps and brute force tactics."</DIV>
<DIV>But that's never been true.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hell rangers have a higher skill level in two-hand slashing than shadowknights (and paladins) which is a skill they will never really use and the knights' bread and butter. Our epics, Pallies and SKs,&nbsp;are two-handed and you rarely see a knight without a two-handed weapon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All other hybrid have skills, AAs, spells, disciplines to crank up their dps either over an extended period of time or with a realitively quick recovery time. But shadowknights do not. </DIV>
<DIV>Paladins have their slay undead with AAs to mega crit those hits 10-12 times in a row for up to several thousands points of damage for each crit. </DIV>
<DIV>Rangers have true shot giving them the ability to have high crit shots with their arrows that can and do reach in the thousands of hps of damage a shot. And true shot has a somewhat reasonable recovery time.</DIV>
<DIV>Beastlord have their pets which are absolute monsters of damage and their beastial fury discipline which jacks up their hits. If they normally hit for say 50, it will jack it up to 150-200 per hit.</DIV>
<DIV>Shadowknights have harm touch, which while it can crit up to 9k, harm touch is not a skill that can be used realistically through any extended period of time. Harm touch recovers only once every 90 minutes or 56 minutes if we max out our AAs. Shadowknights are the opposite of Paladins, their equal or opposite if you will, to harm touch is lay of hands. And that's almost a complete heal for them. Lay of hands is also in addition to their other skills and dps versus undead.</DIV>
<DIV>Shadowknights have no other abilities to increase our damage and nothing that even comes close to matching the damage of other hybrids. Why can't Shadowknights have an AA for slay the living that would work in the same way slay undead does for Paladins?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Look I'm not asking for the world I don't want full necromancer powers, I don't want to&nbsp;play a necromancer I want to play a shadowknight. Nor do I want Rogue dps but I have dedicated much time to my shadowknight (since Kunark was released) and&nbsp;I'd like a little bit of reward for it. I would like shadowknights to be on the same playing field at least as the other hybrid classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kraaliss Ironscale - 69 Shadowknight </DIV>
<DIV>The Seventh Hammer</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
