			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<FONT size=2>"Some of our classes can solo effectively, while others can't. We plan to make changes to classes that struggle with soloing to allow them some solo play. These changes will be made to only affect their abilities while solo and not affect how they perform in groups." <BR><BR>-This is a very good idea, I like it. I often solo rather than finding a group due to my play times. <BR>-A possible suggestion is to give all classes, and their pets, mitigation boosts, possibly increased healing/spell damage potency while they are ungrouped. Unlike how it has been suggested that warriors have improved mitigation while an ability is active, instead make this ability innate for all classes while they are ungrouped. <BR>-An increased mana and health regeneration rate while on a clear aggro list may also help reduce down time since we are often self buffed. <BR>-Another idea is to offer increased EXP while solo'ing. The best EXP seems to come from creatures with in 5 levels of us. This is nearly impossible to solo at high levels with out kiting, a technique that has been clearly frowned upon by the designers. <BR><BR>"Add healing potions to the game. To prevent this from unbalancing the group game, we need to be careful how these potions work. They may need to be a healing potion that does heal-over-time and does not stack with any other healing spells." <BR><BR>-Bad idea, potions cost money. They are often of relitive difficulty to obtain, espically at lower levels. How many "newbies" have the ability to use gate potions and SpiritOfWolf potions? <BR>__________________ <BR><BR>"We will be increasing the availability of pet focus items, particularly for the more casual players." <BR><BR>-Revamp LDoN and put these in as augments. Many of us enjoy LDoN but do not play due to the lack of a reward. It has been said in the past by SoE that playing in LDoN at high levels is past our trivial, but so is it for guilds that raid Vxed Thal. We enjoy the content but LDoN is instanced and yields the benefit of instances. This way people can get uptodate gear with appropiate challanges. LDoN augments would be a good way to get these abilities to these classes with out making them raid or grind through DoN progression. <BR>__________ <BR><BR>"We are looking into adding throwing quivers that grant innate haste similar to normal quivers." <BR><BR>-I have said since the day Zerkers came out and I will say it again and again until it happens. Zerkers are suppose to be able to use large weapons an throw large objects to damage their foes. Summoning items is the only way to effectivly be able to use throwing weapons as a Zerker, especially since many of the throwing items they use require a forge. <BR>Zerkers should have an "endless throwing quiver" similar to that of rangers. <BR>_________ <BR><BR>"The ability would get its own button similar to abilities such as backstab or track. You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 5 minutes" <BR><BR>-5 minuates is too long. Every 1-2 minuates is much more reasonable. The role of a druid in the group can also be that of a back up healer if there is a cleric present. Often on over pulls the cleric may die before the adds can be effictivly controlled. The Druid becomes the main healer. With a 5 minuate recast time the Druid cannot switch to a main healer stance effectivly. A 1-2 minuate down time is more reasonable since that is how long it takes to kill and pull the next creature. <BR>________ <BR><BR>"We will add higher level upgrades to the Word of Morell spell line." <BR><BR>-This shouldn't have taken a patch. This spell is increadibly important. With the nerfs to charm, and the lack of this spell previously, charming has become all risk and no reward. However, it is not limited to just charming. This spell needs to be added asap. <BR><BR>Charming - "This presented some new problems though, the largest of which is you like to haste and buff your pets to get the most out of them and when the charm breaks, you face a much more powerful NPC. We have a plan to ensure charms usefulness and want to gather your opinion before putting it into motion." <BR><BR>-The nerfs to charming make little to no sense. The charmed NPC's have been nerfed so much in most cases that they have become far more risk than reward. Enchanters charms are nerfed so much that the DPS of thier pets is hardly exceeding that of mages. Considering the risk involved with charming vs. the 0 risk of a mage pet, the comparison of charms being over powered is unfair. Even if the pet is not hasted, the casual chanter will not survive a charm break without an increadible amount of luck. The risk needs to be greatly reduced or the nerfs to charmed pets needs to be undone. Remember, risk vs. reward. Charmed pets may be powerful, but the risk is equally high. <BR><BR>"We want charm to be an integral part of your gameplay. You should be able to grab a charmed pet in most circumstances and use that to benefit your group." <BR><BR>-Very few enchanters can handle an unbuffed pet. The only one's greatly benefiting from the power of these pets in group situations is the raid enchanters that have an extreme amount of power. The creatures these enchanters are charming are often trivial to them. The casual player is being pushed even further from charming every time the effictiveness of charm is nerfed and the risk goes untouched. <BR>_________ <BR><BR>Paladins/SK's "With DoN, you gained a limited form of defensive. We are monitoring your feedback and if you like this direction; we plan to make it a full spell line that begins at the level warriors get the defensive discipline." <BR><BR>-These abilities use to much EDU. <BR>________ <BR><BR>Rogues - "We are looking into adding throwing quivers that grant innate haste similar to how normal quivers work" <BR><BR>-Perhaps they should be given endless quiver as well if rogues are suppose to be taking a DPS standpoint with throwing. Throwing for most people is only effective for pulling. It is overly difficult to DPS at high levels with throwing items and no way to get more with out running to the nearest forge. <BR>___________ <BR><BR>"All spells will check for immunity before they are cast. So if the target is immune, the spell will not generate aggro for the caster." <BR><BR>-This is something that is going to be devistating to the Paladin and Shadowkinght classes. They depend highly on those spells, even if the creature is immune, to generate aggro while tanking. This is something that might need to be omitted for those two classes or reconsidered. Many warriors often use stun procs to generate aggro as well. <BR><BR>-This is very helpful for DPS that wishes to use procs with a stun componet and casters trying to debuff. Nothing is more annoying that dying to a creature from slow or mez immunity. <BR>__________ <BR><BR>-I would love to be able to solo more effectivly. The worst part about solo'ing, besides the ability to kill anything that yields EXP at high levels, is the downtime between fights. Very few classes have the means to regenerate health or mana while only self buffed. Again, a doubled or trippled mana, hp, and EDU regen rate while on a clear aggro list would be wonderful. <BR>________ <BR><BR>-67 enc <BR>-57 rng &lt;-- My solo'ing concern<BR>-33 brd <BR>-28 nec</FONT><BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=3>1st SOE forumns post =)</FONT></DIV>
