<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=361#M361">140</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<P><FONT face=Verdana color=#3366cc>Concerning Enchanter changes.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana color=#3366cc>Coming from a high end raiding enchanter main, lvl 70.</FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Verdana color=#336600>c.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We would like to add innate buff effects to enchanter charm spells.&nbsp; While an NPC is under the effects of the charm, they will also be under the effect of spells similar to what you would use to buff your pet.&nbsp; When charm breaks those effects will go away so you are only dealing with the NPC in its base state.</FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=Verdana color=#3366cc>This is a great I like it. </FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Verdana color=#336633>d.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The change mentioned above would cause further imbalance in zones where NPCs dont currently lower their stats when charmed, the changes that were made in Omens will need to be made across the rest of the game and this will be the way new charm works in all of Norrath.</FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=Verdana color=#3366cc>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is shortsighted and not well thought out. You all are realy asking for chanters to up and quit EQ (and not to eq2 mind you), those that havent already left that couldnt take the repeated mauls we have gotten with the nerf bat. You dont *fix* a problem by breaking something that works fine. When I saw OOW charm nerfs I was pissed. But whatever, I just DON'T charm there.. at all.. in any way. It's not useful. May as well deem it un-charmable as far as I am concerned because to me, it is. A good deal of chanters feel the same way, some may not... </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana><FONT color=#3366cc>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I won't just protest without adding some suggestion on how to remedy&nbsp;this, however. With the charm-buff you propose it could make it viable (with some fine tuning and learning to charm difrently) to charm solo in OOW. Since the main concern with this is that to implement this charm-buff you will in turn, nerf existing charm in all other zones where the problem that lead to this *fix* is not even an issue. </FONT><EM><FONT color=#cc3366>Perhaps, to only include this charm-buff in spells that charm mobs lvls 65+ and make these spells not able to work on mobs lvl 64 and lower, would be a happy meduim.&nbsp;&nbsp;Charms up to Comand of Druzzil would&nbsp;remain the same, those above can be&nbsp;re-worked with the charm buff added and&nbsp;reverse&nbsp;level cap 64 and lower. Simple.&nbsp;</FONT></EM></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana color=#3366cc>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This would correct the issue with OOW charms as well as leaving existing charm content that is not problematic well enough alone. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#cc0066>Soete 70 Enc, Saryrn</FONT></P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
