			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
bt wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Two spells.&nbsp; Pretty dynamic.&nbsp; And I messed up on the CHs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Cleric inComplete heal (complete heal):</DIV>
<DIV>7500 hp 400 mana</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druid inComplete heal (Karana's Renewal):</DIV>
<DIV>4680&nbsp;hp 600 mana</DIV>
<DIV>+25% for proposed change</DIV>
<DIV>5850 hp 600 mana</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lets look at this productively.&nbsp; Clerics want to be more dynamic (i.e. less boring) and an option to solo or add some dps.&nbsp; Druids want to heal better in group and raid situations.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druids and clerics obviously have 2 different viewpoints as we are on opposite sides of the fense and both think the other's grass is greener.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PS, how many druids who complain about healing actually specialized in alteration?</DIV>
<P>Message Edited by bt on <SPAN class=date_text>03-15-2005</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>05:15 PM</SPAN></P>
<P>Message Edited by bt on <SPAN class=date_text>03-15-2005</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>05:19 PM</SPAN><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I think you are overlooking some very key elements Bt. 1st taking your own example the druid ch actually cost 150% of the mana cost of the clerics&nbsp;ch (which clerics get at levl 38 i believe and dont get any upgrade for until they are able to start doing aa. At that point their aa's affect the amount healed by their ch&nbsp; and through aa and foci the clerics ch is able to keep pace with the hp inflation of higher level tanks. The druid ch you spoke of is an upgraded version of our lower ich. Now this is the big difference, aa and foci have no effect on it. Other than the aa allowing us to save mana if we specialize in alteration. a druid with all his healing aa and uber foci will still be hard capped, so we pay 150% the mana cost for less healing ability than a level 38 cleric. Yes we do have ways to compensate by getting glowing runes (aincient clorobon) but only the top teir druids have access to those spell becuase a) they are no drop, and b) we are inefficient healers at the top end. So for most druids the cure is put out of reach by the problem. This change while it looks kinda kewl on paper, does nothing to solve that basic problem. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Put another way with ft 20, oak, mask, horse&nbsp;and clair i regen about a 100 mana per tick (i know its somewhere around there i have to log on to get exact numbers for ya)or would be able to cast the cleric ch about once every 4 ticks and have a 0 loss of mana, meaning i could do that every 24 secs. Our ch is once every 36 seconds. Now that doesnt seem to bad in todays game where mobs go down in under a minute, but lets bring into the fact that i have no group heal in case someone beside the tank gets agro or there is an overpull, I have no spell to average hp of group and follow with group hot, and i have no way to hot the tank on inc so i can concentrate on agro management heals, basically my only option at that point is my quick heals which burn through my mana pool. My quick heals for the tank till the mob is slowed (which burn through my mana pool). Yes I can still do it, but where a cleric is watching tv, im sweating to keep up.<BR></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>	
