<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=363#M363">142</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Apologies for the long post to follow</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Enchanters:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have thought some more since my earlier post.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This Nerf to enchanters will serioulsy adn adversly effect most players on the whole of Everquest.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You may ask "what is this idiot talking about" I will explain.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As I mentioned earlier I play a lvl 64 Enchanter, now, when I log on to EQ, and look for a group.&nbsp; What do people want?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Simply put, if they want&nbsp;slower, they look for a shaman, Enchanters are second choice.&nbsp; There are more shaman on my server(VS) than there are active enchanters, and there fore hard to get a group as a pure slower.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>DPS,&nbsp;definalty not, Enchanter Nukes are under par with other DPs casters, and NO group will accept a Charmed pet unless it is a Dire Charm pet, and what use is a level 46 pet in a WOS group for example,&nbsp;even if you could find one.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Crowd&nbsp;Control, &nbsp;This is one area where a Chanter excells BUT most high end groups don't require Crowd Control for regular groups.&nbsp; There is always somebody in a group who can pacify or harmony, on the rare occassions that such woudl be needed.&nbsp; If there is an Add then there are many option such as off tanking or root parking etc.&nbsp; All in all a Chanter is nice for CC but no longer a necasary part of grouping.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>KEI, the only ability the people really want an Enchanter for, and you dont get groups on the strength of KEI.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So, what does all that leave a Chanter with.&nbsp; Well the answer to that is two fold, firstly either sit in POK /ooc KEI Available outside main bank, whilst LFG or Go Solo POV while LFG.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Charm soloing for a chanter is great fun, nice experience, keeps you on the edge of your seat, all in all a good reward.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>BUT</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Charm soloing is high risk, By far much higher risk than any other Pet class.&nbsp; SO as, as always been the EQ way&nbsp; High Risk = High Reward.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Chanters are not the best soloers, Necromancers and Driods for example can solo POP tier2 and 3 zones earlier, better and much much safer than Enchanters can.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Most of the proposed class re-envisoning seems to be around making soloing more viable, yet it drastically reduces the Enchanters ability to do just that. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I see will happen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The Enchanter population will decrease, many will quit EQ altogether (I think myself including, along with the 2 accounts in my household) which will mean:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)&nbsp; Kei style buffs will become less reasily available, which will have a knock on effect in so much as players who believe that they can not compete effectively without a KEI will themselves become disalusioned and some may quit while others will change classes. in the long run creating a further class in ballance</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Many of the Enchanters would cancel their account, which would create a revenue loss and a decrease in population, at a time when Sony and UBI both seem to be trying to create more custom for Everquest</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) EQ's biggest "new Customer " Creator has to be Word of mouth.&nbsp; Word of mouth / Reputation for the game would decrease.&nbsp; instead of "come play EQ with me mate its great fun" I for one and I am sure others also would be more likely to say "Everquest used to be great, but it has really gone downhill now" or "EQ was great till they started nerfing everything"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HOW CAN THIS BE FIXED</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is a difficult question.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>for one, if Enchanter Soloiing is to be made impossible / useless / low reward, then all other classes must have the same done,&nbsp;&nbsp; Necromanace and droid DOTS for example must be nerfed to only do half damage.&nbsp; Mage Pets must have their Hit points halved ETC</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lets face it, if that was to happen, Everquest would quickly go the way of Quake 2 (one the internets most popular online game)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So how then can Enchanters avoid a class detroying Nerf whilst still being updated / re- envisioned</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would say, firstly and most hoped for.&nbsp; Sinply don't change Charming, we enjoy our High risk Charming and deserve the High Rewards to go with it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If it is determined to change that, then two things MUST happen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)&nbsp; all Charms become Dire Charm Style, irrelevant of the levl of the MOB, If you want to decrease our Charmed pets down to be more inline with other Pet classes, then we must also have the benifits of the other classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;Charm would then become a gloryfied Summon Monster.&nbsp; Still a very heavy Nerf but perhaps, only perhaps Chanter life may continue</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Give Enchanter a high Level Pet heal in line with other Pet classes. perhaps a lay on hands style.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Make changes to Enchanter Charms effect Enchanters in GRoups, but not whilst soloing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If this nerf is an attempt to make grouping more "atractive" reduce Solo EXperience FOR EVERYBODY again.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>do not single out Enchanters and destory what few fun things we have left.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
