		" 
			>
			<DIV>What about the Paladins below 60?&nbsp; The levels between 45 and 60 are the slowest most horrible levels for a paladin. I play one (at 55) and I've had many many paladins of 60+ say the only way the advanced past to 60+ is because they had friends who were willing to support them in groups where they were basically useless.&nbsp; Our heals are horrible below 58, We can't root or stun half the mobs we attack, we can't solo hardly anything, not even undead half the time.&nbsp; And the Disc we get holyforge, is nearly worthless, on a green undead mob (spectres in Feerott for example) the holy forge went off one time critting for 10 points of damage. yippee skippee.&nbsp; I just read we get some new defensive line from one of the new expansions, but I guess I haven't seen it yet, must be another 60+ upgrade.&nbsp; How about some disciplines for paladins?&nbsp; We only have 4, even shadow knights have more than that, and theirs are actually useful besides.&nbsp; And the only worthwhile weapon innate we get requires hours upon hours of hard questing that, after reading several accounts of previous paladins doing the quest, makes me terrified to even try it for myself.&nbsp;&nbsp; IMHO Paladins are probably the only ineffective class at progressive soloing (for decent moderate slow exp), We can't dps, we can't heal worth anything useful (we can chain heal constantly and keep a warrior alive if we have a good mana pool and KEI)&nbsp; And without the weapons and armour from the new expansions that cost 50k or more we (at 50's level) are nearly ineffective at keeping aggro because everything resists stuns breaks roots and rips through our AC like tissue.&nbsp; I've written many many /feedbacks on this, hopefully we get more than just "a defensive line" which was added to the higher levels and left no thought to those struggling to get through their 50's.</DIV>	
