<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=367#M367">150</a> of 823
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1134 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Please re-read my above post... I love charming and know how to do it, including how to break the pet early to get experience for both (when it's viable).&nbsp; The random numbers given above sound good but in reality are nowhere near truth.&nbsp; Charmed pets absolutely can NOT kill an equivalent mob.&nbsp; Their actual DPS is lowered to very slightly higher than a mage pet (with the added bonus of nearly 1k mana maintenance every time it needs to be recharmed, not counting any buffs you may wish to add).&nbsp; Putting haste on it does not make enough difference for a charmed pet to win, neither does the highly mitigated slows.&nbsp; On average, a charmed pet can get a slowed mob to 75% or so (give or take depending on the zone).&nbsp; It is not just slower or a little harder, and no our nukes cannot compensate.&nbsp; I think a lot of people don't realize the scale that this happened on.&nbsp; Charm isn't just riskier, it doesn't work.&nbsp; Does. not. work.</DIV>
<DIV>I can deal with not being able to solo at all if group desireability is there.&nbsp; It isn't anymore.&nbsp; And that's my point with this, the widespread application of the charm 'changes' will only hurt further, when we're already crippled 65+, and I fear that the increased applicability of beastlords slowing and necros mezzing again will only kill off the class, other than the remaining people who have alts parked in PoK to make plat.&nbsp; I'm not trying to whine and point the finger and say "soandso class is better".&nbsp; I want to be able to group, play, and have fun again and that's all.&nbsp; I want to love my enchanter the way I did when she was "growing up".</DIV>
<DIV>I also think that a lot of events in which charming is used widespread will be hurt by this that people aren't seeing - such as Tipt and the keyholding mob to Txevu.</DIV>
<DIV>When it's all said and done I just want a use for my class besides the clarity line.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
